Miles R. Soldat
Born: 1958

Description: Human male, ~6ft 9in, ~240lbs. 23 years old. Brown hair, straight and thick, reaches just past shoulders. Beard grown natural, no trimming, currently ~2in long. Brown eyes. Western european facial features. Muscular, and sturdily built. Bulked, not finely cut.

Capability: The subject is an avid fighter, well enough versed in firearms and other weaponry use to hold out well against the greater population. The subject is also a relatively capable craftsman, able to work effectively with most tools and equipment, and learns fast.

Feature: High damage resistance and expedient damage regeneration. The subject is significantly more resistant to physical wounding of all manner, the flesh is harder to lacerate and bones hold against significantly higher forces. Subject heals bodily damages at a rate roughly 3x faster than the average human male.

Notes: The subject’s Feature has the tendency to fluctuate with much significance. Current hypothesis: Damage resistance and regeneration is dependent on the emotional state of the subject. Through observation so far it seems that the subject’s Feature works harder when he is agitated or enraged, and returns to its normal levels during states of rest or low arousal.

The subject has a high mental fortitude and exhibits strong will under strain. Torture at Firebase Delta yielded zero information from the subject, not so much as a name.

Luna
Born: 1955

Description: Female anthro; unknown wolf variant. ~7ft 2in, ~250lbs. 26 years old. Fur is a fairly consistent shade of dark grey, roughly 1in long across the body. Head hair is a shade of light grey, nearly silver, long and coarse, it grows along the shoulders as well as back and tapers down in width and in length roughly half way down. Front chest and stomach are colored in the same grey-silver, the same length as body fur, a slight plumage of longer fur is present between the breasts. Grey fur peppers the muzzle. Blue eyes. Skin is black. Subject is muscular, with a moderate layer of fat on the abdomen, buttock, and upper legs, as well as on other parts of the body. Subject is shapely and clearly feminine, strength is still apparent, however.

Feature: None discernable at this time.

Notes: The subject is an avid magic user, observation has shown usage to commune with and command the natural world, as well as to induce berserkir rage states. It seems that she is a druidic-barbaric practitioner of sorts? Unsure at this time, further observation is required.
